        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 8 at 12:16AM CDT until June 8 at 7:00AM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL",
        "description": "* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is occurring.\n\n* WHERE...Portions of Alabama, including the following counties,\nJackson and Madison and southern middle Tennessee, including the\nfollowing county, Lincoln.\n\n* WHEN...Until 700 AM CDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Streams continue to rise due to excess runoff from\nearlier rainfall.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 1215 AM CDT, Emergency management reported flooding in the\nwarned area. Flooding is already occurring. Between 4 and 8\ninches of rain have fallen.\n- Flooding impacts will continue, but no additional rainfall is\nexpected.\n- Some locations that will experience flooding include...\nNorthern Huntsville, Scottsboro, Moores Mill, Meridianville,\nHazel Green, Stevenson, Hollywood, Skyline, Gurley, Section,\nWoodville, Pisgah, New Market, Alabama A And M University,\nHarvest, Lincoln, Pleasant Groves, Hytop, Dutton and Paint\nRock.",
        "instruction": "Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the\ndangers of flooding.",
